  "body": "#üêû Bug Report\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nI restarted my node with this exact command:\r\n```c:/prysm/prysm.bat beacon-chain --datadir=c:/prysm --dev --pprof```\r\n\r\nMy node was synced right before to restart it, but still when it started, I had around 30.000 slots behind the beacon chain. I waited it to be fully synced, then I restarted it again, and I got the same result:\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/23481418/83944326-0a560800-a803-11ea-8993-f35fa42b122c.png)\r\n\r\nAlso after syncing, it deleted a lot of old state, which shows that the db hasn't been saved at all\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/23481418/83944367-47ba9580-a803-11ea-9e50-41136744f24b.png)\r\n\r\n### Has this worked before in a previous version?\r\n\r\nI never had this issue in previous version (alpha 8 and bellow). It seems like the current state of the db is not correctly save or something.\r\n\r\n## üî¨ Minimal Reproduction\r\n\r\nOnly restart the beacon node (maybe `--dev` is needed to reproduce the bug)\r\n\r\n## üî• Error\r\n\r\n N/A\r\n\r\n## üåç  Your Environment\r\n\r\n**Operating System:**\r\nWindows 10 Home\r\n\r\n**What version of Prysm are you running? (Which release)**\r\nAlpha 9, using prysm.bat",
