    "body": "I know what happened. In:\r\n\r\n- Alpha.8: Default `--slots-per-archived-point` is 256 slots\r\n- Alpha.9: Default `--slots-per-archived-point` is 2048 slots (I should never have increased this inflight. Bad idea)\r\n\r\nNow the archived index structure in DB is messed up. The node thinks it has more archived indices than it should. Hence it's not saving new archived index at every 2048 interval. To work around, theres two options:\r\n\r\n1.) Resync from genesis with `--dev` flag\r\n2.) Add `--slots-per-archive-point=256` with `--dev`\r\n\r\nMy action item from this:\r\n1.) Prevent UX to change archived index midflight\r\n\r\n@GuillaumeMiralles can you confirm either option works for you? \r\n",
